content.rendered:
NASA Mars Settlement Competition

What is this page about?

This page contains analysis from UKSDC volunteers on designs that reached the later stages of the NASA centennial challenge: 3D printed Mars Habitat Competition. All of the designs are obviously of incredible quality having reached the phase 2 and phase 3 stages of a NASA competition and we do not expect to see stuff near this quality, but it should help to give you all a variety of ideas. This helps to show you that there are a huge variety of viable options for handling any Request for Proposal, and this should inspire you to be creative in your approach to tackling this competition. 

This page is a constant work in progress as volunteers find time to fill in their opinions on each design, but even just the videos themselves, particularly those with 2 videos showing design progression, should be of great help to competitors!

Hassell + Eckersley O'Callaghan
